<div class="problem-strip" id="problem">
  <div class="problem-grid container">
    <div class="problem-left">
      <div class="section-tag">The Problem</div>
      <h2 class="section-heading">Your digital presence<br/><span class="accent">is costing you clients.</span></h2>
      <p>
        Most professional firms in Kenya have a website — built years ago, never updated, sitting there
        doing nothing. Meanwhile, potential clients are forming opinions the moment they search your name.
      </p>
    </div>
    <ul class="problem-list">
      <li>
        <span class="problem-num">01</span>
        <div>
          <strong>No Google presence</strong>
          Referrals search you before they call. If your GBP is empty or nonexistent, they find a competitor instead.
        </div>
      </li>
      <li>
        <span class="problem-num">02</span>
        <div>
          <strong>Outdated website</strong>
          A stale WordPress site from 2017 signals that your business isn't growing. Design builds trust before the first meeting.
        </div>
      </li>
      <li>
        <span class="problem-num">03</span>
        <div>
          <strong>No consistent content</strong>
          Your competitors are posting, ranking, and getting found. Silence is losing ground.
        </div>
      </li>
      <li>
        <span class="problem-num">04</span>
        <div>
          <strong>Manual follow-up</strong>
          Enquiries go cold because no one has time to chase them. Automation fixes this without hiring.
        </div>
      </li>
    </ul>
  </div>
</div>
